{"author":{"id":"7f425f6756bada4a45c1ebab00019b7e63109e45ffe78970e6539e70705964b5"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769632080,"nonce":"TNg/MGPU04d80oXJ2wQ/bZJLnpM=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s7mgcd8","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7630","origin":"github"},"title":"lastz with PAF output fails","message":"Recently I updated the lastz config to allow PAF output because JBrowse 2 can take PAF as an input. This fails on test with the message `Can't understand \"--format=PAF-\"`. The trailing dash looks very suspicious to me. The actual command from the bug email is\n```\nlastz   '/cvmfs/data.galaxyproject.org/byhand/hg38/seq/hg38.2bit'    \u003c(gunzip -c \n'/jetstream2/scratch/test/jobs/1506985/inputs/dataset_24944804-06b4-49df-b4ec-7748d0cdfc87.dat')    \n '--strand=both'      '--gap=600,150' '--ambiguous=iupac'           '--filter=identity:90..100'    \n --traceback=160M    --format=PAF- --action:target=multiple --rdotplot=plot.r \u003e '/jetstream2/scratch/test/jobs/1506985/outputs/dataset_101e4bd9-a0d7-4796-8ac4-cb3f8ff7d376.dat' \u0026\u0026 Rscript \n/jetstream2/scratch/test/jobs/1506985/configs/tmp2lmg9krg \u003e /dev/null 2\u003e\u00261\n```\nwhere you can see the PAF- as the format. I tried to exactly mimic the config BLASTN as an output format, and BLASTN has a trailing dash, and running lastz with BLASTN as the selected format works. So I am at a loss as for what to do. The obvious choice would be to just strip the - out of the config:\n\nhttps://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/157d1ec643c7e13aee19723bebcb97ce3a4ce29d/tools/lastz/lastz.xml#L260-L263\n\nbut I'm not sure that blindly doing stuff is the way to go.","files":null}]}